  "text": "Recently, the therapeutic use of osmotic agents, such as hypertonic saline (HS) has been proposed to aid in mucus clearance in patients with CF [CITATION_1] . Inhaled HS may increase airway surface fluid, reduce the abnormal surface adhesivity and tenacity of the mucus and improve MCC. In addition, HS may induce cough, thereby promoting cough clearance.",
